title: For Sale:  US Army Gen 3 sleeping bag set (x3 bags)
postcontent:
Well after trying to buy a sleeping bag system online and getting a stinky ripped up one, i decided to drive to Ohio and go to the government auction site where I could pick through them one by one and check all the components. The upside is that I got a sleeping bag system that I lived in for 8 years in the Army with three deployments and endless camping, hiking and hunting trips. The downside is that for the best price possible I had to buy an entire crate of the things. Anyways each set has been inspected inside and out for damage, they're all fantastic and lightly used (and I was issued a well used one so I know the difference) these things are super comfy and military durable. 

Each comes with a stuff sack and three bags. 1 waterproof goretex bivvy bag with woodland camo, 1 inclimate weather bag (patrol bag), and 1 heavy winter bag. Each bag has heavy duty zippers on the inside and out, and snaps to allow venting if it's too warm zipped up. The sleeping bags also have built in hoods with bungee tensioners. 

I've got extensive use out of all bags in varying climates around the world. At 6'3" and 250lbs I've never had trouble getting comfy, even sleeping in my armor and boots with my m4.

Don't roll the dice on getting a Chinese clone on eBay, or a worn out spank tank from a surplus shop for 400 bucks. This stuff was clearly issued to pogues who never used because they never went to the field or deployed.

Discount for vets. Huge discount for 2ID vets. :)

title: For Sale:  80% lower finishing
postcontent:
Need to finish an 80% AR-15 or .308 AR lower but don't have a jig or machine?  Don't want to make the investment just to build one or two?   Intimidated by the task at hand?  I can help you out!

For $50, you get my guidance and the use of a full size DRO'd 3 HP Lagun vertical knee mill, along with the correct cutters.  Yes, you have to operate the machine; I can't legally finish the lower for you.  But I will walk you through the process so that your project turns into a rifle with a professional finish in the fire control pocket instead of a paperweight.

Expect to spend about 60-90 minutes completing your 80% lower on my machines with my help.  This is not one of those CNC operations where you just clamp the lower in a fixture and push a button (which ATF has frowned upon). This is a manual mill with digital scales.  I have worked up a cheat sheet that accounts for cutter radius; you won't need to do any math, it's basically color by numbers.

Just to reiterate for the legal eagles: You are not paying me to finish your lower receiver; you are paying to rent my time and equipment.

Yes, you have to come here.  This mill weighs 3,600 pounds and requires 3 phase or phase converted power.  I cannot bring the machine to you, not even for extra cash.

postcontent:
1000 rounds - Danish AMA 5.56 NATO M855 / SS109 62gr Tungsten Steel Core Penetrators

Danish Military contract ammo for use by all NATO countries, similar to Federal Lake City M855 Green Tip. SS109 is the international code given to M855 mil-spec ammo made outside the USA .

As with LC M855, this ammo has annealed case necks, necks & primers are both sealed, primers are also staked & necks crimped per mil spec. They also have the *NATO CROSS* head stamp to verify mil-spec quality compliance.

This is accurate compared to other SS109/M855 & ranks among the better lots of Lake City M855 ammo & possibly the best of foreign manufactured SS109.

These come packaged in plain white boxes of 50 rounds each. Each 50 rounds is loaded on 10 round plastic stripped clips sealed in air & water tight plastic sleeves, each 10rd stripper clip is separate airtight into 5 individual perforated sections so you can open part of a package & still maintain the long term storage of the ammo on the other on stripper clips. All 750 rounds are in 15 boxes of 50 rounds, in a plain white box sealed with packing tape as I received it from Ammoman's website in 2013. Head stamps are years 2010-2012. I also have some opened boxes still sealed in the plastic if you want a full 1000 rounds, just let me know.

This is perfect ammo for long term storage to put back for a rainy day. As it's already sealed in airtight plastic (as well as the standard Mil-spec primer & case neck sealant) all you need to do is put it into a metal or sturdy plastic ammo box in a stable environment that's relatively cool. This LNIB service pistol is the spitting image of the Beretta Model 92FS (with a few improvements) and sells for $100 to $150 less than the glamorous Italian’s price tag.

When Taurus made the first PT-92 in 1980, they didn’t copy or reverse-engineer the Beretta Model 92F as is sometimes believed. Instead, they bought Beretta’s entire Brazilian factory in Sao Paulo with its machinery, parts and plans. They even kept Beretta’s trained workers at their stations. 

Taurus has specially designed a drop hammer forged ordnance grade alloy frame that won't crack or allow the slide to come off. They’ve also included a three-position frame-mounted ambidextrous safety, which is more secure than a slide mounted safety, and allows for a classic SA "cocked-and-locked" mode, as well as functioning as a DA de-cocking lever. With the 3 dot fixed combat sight model 92 you'll be able to face any situation without compromise.

In all aspects of its fit and machining, the Taurus is every bit as good as the much costlier Beretta Model 92FS it’s patterned after. The Taurus’ metal finish is smooth and even. And Taurus uses a stainless-steel guide rod rather than the Beretta’s plastic rod.

Don't be fooled and get raped paying $350 for 500 rounds or even $250 for 500 rounds of 223 or 556! Cabelas has been running sales, free shipping and only $.027 to .029 cents a round! Why pay more than 50 cents here for the exact same?
HK Buyers BEWARE!  HK has a $200 rebate on them new! NEW prices are below what trolls here are posting new plus you get another $200 off that!
HKSpecialtystore.com is simply one example...  search around for legit sellers and find great deals this Holiday season. Oh yea... I've been buying 22lr for about 5 cents per round shipped to my door... not the 10 cent plus found here.
try Slickguns.com to see what real deals are like!
I am not against this site here... I find some good honest deals from honest sellers... but there are too many trolls, private and stores posting here raping people in my mind... 
Happy Holidays* Shop wisely and save!
